songs.title: Hell Yeah Baby
songs.lyrics:
[Intro: Charli XCX]
Ay, ha!

[Verse 1: Charli XCX]
Pull up, pull up
Bass in the trunk
Valet gon' pick up, pick up
Hop out the Benz
Freaking weekend
Dressed to the nines, lookin' like tens

[Pre-Chorus 1: Charli XCX]
Quick, snap a pic, then go
Walk through the club past the velvet rope
Got a manicured man on my manicure hand
Oh, damn, it's my song on the stereo
And it goes like...

[Chorus: Charli XCX]
Na-na-na-na-na-na-na-na-na
I'm drunk, and I'm on a roll
Na-na-na-na-na-na-na-na
He said, "Girl, can I take you home?"
And I was like...
Ha-ha, hell yeah, baby
Ha-ha, hell yeah, baby
Ha-ha, hell yeah, baby
Ha-ha, let's go

[Verse 2: Charli XCX]
Pull up, pull up
Don't give a fuck
My girls gon' switch up, switch up
Here in the crowd
Wearing the crown
Me and my man gon' get down, get down

[Pre-Chorus 2: Charli XCX]
Walk to the bathroom stall
Wanna push him hard up against that wall
Might be spilling my glass, but I got that class
So I'm gonna make him wait if he wants it all
And it goes like...

[Chorus: Charli XCX]
Na-na-na-na-na-na-na-na-na
I'm drunk, and I'm on a roll
Na-na-na-na-na-na-na-na
He said, "Girl, can I take you home?"
And I was like...
Ha-ha, hell yeah, baby
Ha-ha, hell yeah, baby
Ha-ha, hell yeah, baby
Ha-ha, let's go

[Bridge: Ryn Weaver and Charli XCX]
Oh, boys, they try to shout
They hoot and holla when they can
They see me out
Too bad I'm leaving with my...
My man, man
But if you ain't got one, take a stand, stand
Single ladies in the club, it's your jam jam
But if you got a ring on it, wave your hand, hand
Like a boss
Like a boss
Like a boss
Like a boss, boss, boss, boss, bossy, bossy

[Chorus: Charli XCX]
Na-na-na-na-na-na-na-na-na
I'm drunk, and I'm on a roll
Na-na-na-na-na-na-na-na
He said, "Girl, can I take you home?"
And I was like...
Ha-ha, hell yeah, baby
Ha-ha, hell yeah, baby
Ha-ha, hell yeah, baby
Ha-ha, let's go
Ha-ha, hell yeah, baby
Ha-ha, hell yeah, baby
Ha-ha, hell yeah, baby
Ha-ha, let's go

[Outro: Charli XCX]
Hell yeah, baby
Hell yeah, baby
Hell yeah, baby
Let's go
